title: Quasifree Knockout In O-16(P,2P)N-15 At An Incident Energy of 151 Mev.

x4freetext: QUASIFREE KNOCKOUT IN O-16(P,2P)N-15 AT AN INCIDENT
ENERGY OF 151 MEV.

x4codes.hlp: Southern Universities Nuclear Insstitute, Faure, South Africa, Rep.
University of Maryland, College Park, MD, United States of America

x4freetext: FEC

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.44, p.329 (1991)

x4freetext: .THE THREE DETECTOR TELESCOPE WERE
ARRANGED IN AN INPLANE CONFIGURATION WITH ONE TELESCOPE
ON A MOVABLE ARM ON ONE SIDE OF THE BEAM,AND THE OTHER
TWO TELESCOPES (SEPARATED BY 15 DEGREES) MOUNTED ON A
SECOND MOVABLE ARM WHICH COVERED AN ANGULAR RANGE OF 50
TO 70 DEGREES ON THE OTHER SIDE. DOUBLE-APERTURE BRASS
COLLIMATORS IN FRONT OF EACH DETECTOR TELESCOPE (1-MM
SI SURFACE-BARRIER DETECTOR, FOLLOWED BY 51-MM DIAMETER
BY127-MM-LONG NAI CRYSTAL-PHOTOTUBE ASSEMBLY WITH A
THIN ENTRANCE WINDOW) DEFINED THE EFFECTIVE TARGET
LENGTHS AND SOLID ANGLES.
THE OXYGEN GAS ( >99.9 PER CENT PURITY,99.8 PER CENT
O-16) WAS CONTAINED IN A CYLINDRICAL GAS CELL OF
DIAMETER 10 CM AND HEIGHT 4 CM, WITH ENTRANCE AND EXIT
WINDOWS OF 6-MUM HAVAR FOIL.

x4codes.hlp: Southern Universities Nuclear Insstitute, Faure, South Africa, Rep.

x4freetext: . SEPARATED-SECTOR CYCLOTRON.
/BY COMPILER/.ENERGY-SHARING DISTRIBUTIONS,I.E.,
DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR THE INDIVIDUAL RESIDUAL
STATES PLOTTED AS A FUNCTION OF THE KINETIC ENERGY OF
ONE OF THE DETECTED PROTONS ARE GIVEN IN DATA-SECTION.
E IS KINETIC ENERGY. E-ERR IS DATA-POINT READER
UNCERTAINTY FOR E.
.DISTORED-WAVE IMPULSE APPROXIMATION.
A WEAK-COUPLING NUCLEAR STRUCTURE.AVERAGE SPECTROSCOPIC
FACTORS.
THE UNCERTAINTY OF THE ABSOLUTE CROSS-SECTION SCALES
IS LESS THAN 10%.
.BY CAJAD.
